# ReelCaster Frontend - Project Structure

## Overview
This is a Next.js 15.3.4 frontend application with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and the App Router architecture.

## Directory Structure

### Core Application
- [src/app/](mdc:src/app) - Next.js App Router directory containing pages, layouts, and route components
- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component that wraps all pages
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Homepage component
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global CSS styles and Tailwind imports

### Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts (uses pnpm as package manager)
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases (`@/*` â†’ `./src/*`)
- [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs) - ESLint configuration extending Next.js and TypeScript rules
- [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs) - PostCSS configuration for Tailwind CSS

### Public Assets
- [public/](mdc:public) - Static assets served from the root domain

## File Organization Conventions

### Pages and Layouts
- Use the App Router convention: create directories under `src/app/` for routes
- Page components should be named `page.tsx`
- Layout components should be named `layout.tsx`
- Loading components should be named `loading.tsx`
- Error components should be named `error.tsx`

### Component Organization
- Create components in `src/components/` (to be created as needed)
- Use PascalCase for component files and directories
- Group related components in subdirectories
- Export components as default exports

### Utility Functions
- Create utilities in `src/lib/` or `src/utils/` (to be created as needed)
- Use camelCase for utility functions
- Group related utilities in modules

## Import Conventions
- Use the `@/` path alias for imports from the `src/` directory
- Example: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button'`
- Prefer named exports for utilities and hooks
- Use default exports for React components
